.TH WL-KBD 1 "April 2026" "wl-kbd 0.1"
.SH NAME
wl-kbd \- Keyboard layout indicator for Wayland sessions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wl-kbd
.RI [ -f ]
.RI [ -l ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
wl-kbd is a system tray indicator that shows the current keyboard layout.
It supports flag mode and two-letter mode with light/dark letter themes.

The indicator reads keyboard layout changes through Wayland and xkbcommon.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -f
Start in flag mode.
.TP
.B -l
Start in letters mode.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored in
.IR ~/.config/wl-kbd/indicator.ini .

Main keys:
.RS
.nf
[Indicator]
tray_style=FLAG|LETTERS
letter_theme=light|dark
letter_icon_size=24
.fi
.RE

In labwc, switch shortcut hint can be read from:
.IR ~/.config/labwc/environment
via
.BR XKB_DEFAULT_OPTIONS .
.SH FILES
.I ~/.config/wl-kbd/indicator.ini
.RS
User preferences for the indicator.
.RE
.I ~/.config/labwc/environment
.RS
labwc environment variables, including XKB_DEFAULT_OPTIONS.
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR labwc-kbd (1),
.BR labwc (1)
